^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The Stayman Convention is used to find a 4-4 major suit fit in NT auctions. You should only use Stayman if you have an invitational (8-9) or a game forcing hand (10 or more). Do not bid Stayman if you have a minimum (0 to 7 points) hand. Further, your hand should meet any of the following criteria:|
PG| ***** 9 ***** |


cs|1|cp|4|AT|

{  You have one 4-card major  }|
PG| ***** 10 ***** |


AT|

{  You have two 4-card majors  }|
PG| ***** 11 ***** |


AT|

{  You have one 4-card major and one 5-card major   }

|
PG| ***** 12 ***** |


cp||AT|
Therefore, with a game forcing and an invitational hand you bid Stayman if you have 5/4 in majors when responding to 1NT opener by partner. |
PG| ***** 13 ***** |


cs||cp||at|

